reviews.review:
An attempt of a boycott is currently underway for Dead by Daylight. For the next 3 months (starting June 2021) we are going to cease all sales, and stop buying everything BHVR releases. This includes cosmetics, rifts, and the next Chapter. BHVR has treated the health of the game poorly and ignored the community for the past 2 years, with it only getting worse and worse. If you are reading this and want DBD, wait for the next 3 months before you get it, and check in to see if anything has changed.

At the time of writing this review - early December 2020 - Behaviour Interactive, the developer and publisher of this game, have become one of the greediest developers I've seen, and I preordered ME: Andromeda, believe me when I speak of greed. BHVR:
1) Continously nerf things that do not require anyone's attention at any given moment;
2) Outright ignore things that make the game unfun for both sides;
3) Turn the live servers into test servers at a moment's notice, just because they feel like it;
4) Release broken, unfinished content ("The Binding of Kin" chapter, to be precise: some 2\6 of the chapter just doesn't work due to bugs, even though those bugs WERE uncovered during the PTB (thanks to players, not the QA department, if there is any), but were completely ignored);
5) Mechanics wise the game hasn't changed in some 2-3 years, but the cosmetic shop is constantly updated with new skins, charms, whatever - anything that can be monetized;
6) The whole progression system is just grind for the sake of grind, since the devs are too afraid to simplify it, fearing that people will stop playing;
7) The Battle Pass system (let's not forget that it exists at all in a full-priced game with DLCs) is even grindier than the base progression, which shouldn't be possible. 

And I'm not even touching upon A L L of the bugs, which at this point in time are features (game lobbies don't load even when you want to play solo, map glitches, audio disappears for certain things, Killer power glitches, Survivor item glitches, etc-etc). 

As much as I adore the design department of BHVR, their actual "game development" and other departments are god-awful, this game is being ruined by its developers as I write this review. After playing for 1k hours I cannot recommend this game to anyone who values their time (and money, if it comes to that).
